When your prayers are answered. 🤍 A little over a year ago I finally saw a positive result on a pregnancy test. After 5 years of trying, 2 rounds of IUI, two rounds of IVF, countless needle pokes, and one very special donor… it was positive. 

It came up immediately and tears started rolling down my cheeks. Pure and absolute joy. 

And I still cry every time I watch these videos. 

Our journey to growing our family was entirely different than I planned. If you’re struggling, I pray you can find some hope in our story. Your path may look different than you thought it would. And that’s okay. I promise you it won’t feel any different when your baby is in your arms the first time. It’s just as magical and just as perfect. 

#ivfbaby #ivfsuccess #babyboy #pregnancyvideo #pregnancyreel #trending #infertilityawareness #infertilityjourney #fertilityjourney #infertilitywarrior

Pre-brunch ➡️ post-brunch. Been under the weather for the last week (those daycare colds are no joke!), but didn’t let it stop me from celebrating MY FIRST MOTHERS DAY! 💕🥹 The boys brought me coffee in the morning and then we did brunch with my family. They gave me the sweetest cards and best of all, so many baby snuggles and laughs. There were months and days I didn’t think this would happen… that I would ever be a mom. So, sometimes it’s still very surreal. I know some of you are still struggling and my heart is with you. If you haven’t read my blog post on our fertility journey I’ll share it in Stories. 2023 ✨ My words for 2023 were strength, purpose, family and love. It was by far my hardest but most beautiful year yet. There were so many times when I felt like a failure, overwhelmed, and the most stressed I’d ever been. But, it’s also the year I learned how to be a mother. What my real priorities are. How blessed I am with my boys. Had some of the biggest smiles and laughs. I fell in love with this new chapter of life. 🤍

The best memories came from all the small moments. And I can’t wait for more in 2024.
